    slug: "mukhtasar-sahih-al-bukhari-2-volume-set",
    description: `Mukhtasar Sahih al-Bukhari is a carefully condensed two-volume set that presents the most important hadith narrations from Sahih al-Bukhari, the most authoritative collection of Prophetic traditions in Islam. The original Sahih al-Bukhari, compiled by the great hadith scholar Imam Muhammad ibn Ismail al-Bukhari (died 256 AH), contains over seven thousand hadith selected from approximately six hundred thousand narrations that he examined during his sixteen-year journey through the Muslim world collecting and verifying the sayings and actions of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). This mukhtasar (abridgement) distils that vast collection into a more manageable format by selecting the most essential narrations and removing some of the repetitive chains of transmission, while preserving the authenticity and completeness of each hadith's meaning and context. The two volumes maintain the original organisational structure of Sahih al-Bukhari, with chapters arranged by topic covering all major aspects of Islamic life, including the pillars of faith (iman), the five pillars of Islam, purification (taharah), the prayer (salah), charity (zakah), fasting (sawm), pilgrimage (hajj), trade and commerce, marriage and divorce, warfare, food and drink, clothing and adornment, medicine, dreams, virtues of the companions, and the merits of various Quranic surahs. The translation and commentary accompanying each hadith help readers understand the context in which the Prophet spoke and the practical implications of his guidance for daily life. The abridgement process was carried out by qualified scholars who ensured that no essential legal, theological, or ethical content was lost in the condensation, making this set a reliable reference for scholars and general readers alike. The two-volume format makes this set more practical and affordable than the full multi-volume edition while still providing a substantial and representative selection of the most authentic hadith in Islam. The books are printed on quality paper with clear typography that makes reading comfortable during extended study sessions, and the binding is designed to withstand the frequent handling that reference works typically receive. This set is particularly valuable for students of Islamic studies who need access to the primary hadith literature but may find the complete Sahih al-Bukhari too voluminous for their immediate needs.`,
    metaDescription: "Mukhtasar Sahih al-Bukhari is a condensed two-volume set presenting essential authentic hadith covering all aspects of Islamic life and practice."
