    slug: "mukhtasar-sahih-bukhari-large-urdu",
    description: `Mukhtasar Sahih Bukhari (Large) is an Urdu-language abridged edition of Sahih al-Bukhari presented in a generous large format that enhances readability and makes it suitable for use in mosques, madrasahs, and study circles where the text needs to be visible to multiple readers. Sahih al-Bukhari, compiled by Imam Muhammad ibn Ismail al-Bukhari (rahimahullah), stands as the most authentic and revered collection of hadith in the entire Islamic tradition, and its status as the most reliable book after the Quran is unanimously accepted by Muslim scholars across all schools of thought. This large-format mukhtasar (abridgement) carefully selects the most important narrations from the complete Sahih al-Bukhari, preserving the essential meaning and legal implications of each hadith while reducing the overall volume to make it more accessible to Urdu-speaking readers who may find the complete multi-volume set prohibitively large. The Urdu translation is rendered in clear and accessible language that accurately conveys both the literal meaning and the contextual nuances of the original Arabic text, making the hadith understandable to readers who may not have advanced Arabic proficiency. The large page size allows for generous line spacing, a comfortable font size, and adequate margins for notes, which is particularly beneficial for elderly readers, for classroom use where the teacher needs to display the book, and for anyone who values readability over compactness. The hadith are organised according to the traditional chapter structure of Sahih al-Bukhari, with sections on faith, knowledge, ablution, prayer, funerals, charity, fasting, pilgrimage, trade, marriage, food, clothing, medicine, and many other topics. Each hadith is presented with its chain of narrators and the complete text, along with brief explanatory notes where the meaning requires clarification for a general audience. The large-format binding uses quality materials that ensure durability even with frequent handling and reference, making this edition suitable for institutional use in mosques and educational settings as well as for personal study at home. This edition represents an excellent balance between completeness and accessibility, providing a substantial selection of the most authentic Prophetic traditions in a format that encourages regular reading and study of the hadith literature.`,
