    slug: "mukhtasir-tafseer-fath-ul-qadeer",
    description: `Mukhtasir Tafseer Fath ul Qadeer is a condensed Urdu-language commentary on the Quran based on the monumental tafseer work "Fath al-Qadeer" by Imam al-Shawkani, one of the most respected exegetical works in Islamic scholarship that draws upon the Quran itself, the authentic hadith, the statements of the companions, and the explanations of the classical scholars to provide a comprehensive understanding of the divine text. The original Fath al-Qadeer is named after the Quranic promise that "We have sent down the Reminder, and We will preserve it," with the title signifying that the Quran is a mighty opening or victory of divine guidance. This mukhtasir (abridged) edition makes the vast scholarship of al-Shawkani accessible to a wider Urdu-speaking audience by condensing the detailed discussions while retaining the essential points of interpretation, the key evidences cited, and the core legal and theological conclusions reached by the original author. The tafseer follows a verse-by-verse approach, explaining the meaning of each verse, its context of revelation (asbab al-nuzul) where relevant, the linguistic nuances of the Arabic text, and the practical lessons and rulings that can be derived from it. The commentary pays particular attention to clarifying the apparent contradictions between verses that critics have raised, demonstrating the internal consistency and coherence of the Quranic message. Where multiple interpretations of a verse exist among the scholars, the author presents the most evidence-based view while noting alternative opinions, giving readers a balanced understanding of the interpretive possibilities. The tafseer addresses legal rulings derived from Quranic verses, including those related to worship, family law, criminal law, financial transactions, and international relations, making it a valuable reference for students of Islamic jurisprudence. The theological dimensions of the Quran are also thoroughly explored, with clear explanations of verses pertaining to the attributes of Allah, the nature of the Hereafter, the stories of the prophets, and the fundamental principles of Islamic belief. The Urdu translation of this abridgement is rendered in clear, scholarly language that maintains the precision of the original Arabic commentary while being accessible to readers who have studied Urdu through formal Islamic education. This volume is an essential addition to any Urdu-speaking Muslim's library, providing a reliable and comprehensive Quranic commentary that combines scholarly depth with practical applicability.`,
    metaDescription: "Mukhtasir Tafseer Fath ul Qadeer is an abridged Urdu Quranic commentary based on al-Shawkani's work with legal and theological insights."
