    slug: "muslim-morals-and-manners-pocket-size",
    description: `Muslim Morals and Manners (Pocket Size) is a compact and portable English-language book that provides a practical guide to the ethical conduct, social etiquette, and personal character traits that Islam expects from every believer. This pocket-sized edition is specifically designed for maximum portability, allowing it to be carried in a pocket, purse, bag, or car compartment so that its guidance is always within reach for reference throughout the day. The book addresses the comprehensive Islamic concept of akhlaq (morals and character), which the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) identified as the primary purpose of his mission when he stated that he was sent to perfect good character. The content is organised thematically, covering the major areas of moral conduct that a Muslim encounters in daily life. The section on personal character discusses virtues such as honesty (sidq), truthfulness, patience (sabr), gratitude (shukr), humility (tawadu'), contentment (qana'ah), modesty (haya), courage (shaja'ah), and generosity (sakha'), providing Quranic verses and hadith narrations that establish each virtue as a religious obligation and a means of drawing closer to Allah. The book also addresses the prohibited character traits and behaviours that Islam condemns, including lying, backbiting (ghibah), slander, envy (hasad), pride (kibr), anger, greed, and stinginess, explaining both the spiritual harm caused by these traits and the practical steps for overcoming them. The section on social manners covers the Islamic etiquette for greeting others, visiting the sick, attending funerals, sharing food, honouring guests, respecting elders, caring for children, maintaining ties of kinship, treating neighbours kindly, and interacting with non-Muslims. The book addresses workplace ethics, business conduct, and the Islamic principles of fair trade and honest dealings. The manners of speech are covered in detail, including the prohibition of obscene language, the importance of speaking gently, the virtue of remaining silent when one has nothing beneficial to say, and the proper etiquette of giving advice and correcting others. The pocket-size format includes a quick-reference section that summarises the most important etiquette rules in a condensed format, making it easy to consult in specific situations. The English text is written in clear and accessible language that communicates the Islamic ethical vision without requiring prior knowledge of Arabic or Islamic terminology. This compact reference is an ideal companion for Muslims of all ages and backgrounds who wish to improve their character and conduct in accordance with the teachings of Islam.`,
